{
  "texts": [
    "The use of NER in social media is one particular instance of its usage that Jehangir et al. (2023) highlights.",
    "Every day, social media networks produce enormous amounts of data, frequently in the form of loosely structured microblogs.",
    "From this noisy and unstructured data, NER assists in removing relevant entities that can be used for additional research, such as Sentiment Analysis or topic identification.",
    "To enable more focused and pertinent data processing, NER, for example, may recognize when a person, business, or place is mentioned in a tweet or social media post.",
    "NLG technologies enable machines to produce coherent and contextually relevant text."
  ]
}